Time-of flight for prompt neutron`s energy
measurement on flight base 75.8 cm, and fission
fragments energy measurement on flight base 31.9 cm
Two types of coincidence were used
was used to separate prompt neutrons and
fragment(FF1) energy measurement, active area 900 cm2,
FF1 signal starts all time-of-flight system
Liquid organic scintillator NE213 in 12.8 cm
container with 5 cm thick walls, Time resolution
1.5 nanosec, for neutron detection. The neutron
threshold level of the detector was set at 0.2 MeV
using the gamma ray from Na-22 source
.The purified 239Pu was electrodeposited on a 90 micro-
gram/cm2 thick nickel foil with copper backing.
Radiochemical purity of 239Pu is more than 99% in
all Pu isotopes. Pu-239 thickness is 45 microgram/cm2
.Correction for the number of neutrons emitted from
FF1 events was made using the evaluated mass
(see `REL-REF` keyword), for the energy loss of the
fragments in the 239Pu target with the nickel backing
MEMO CP-D/635. In other SAN BIB information and
